article.description: Dawn Evans scored 27 points and had 12 assists to lead No. 25 James Madison to an 86-54 win over Lafayette on Tuesday night in the semifinals of the JMU Invitational.
article.headline: No. 25 James Madison buries Lafayette
article.linkText: Evans has double-double; James Madison rolls
article.story:
HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Dawn Evans scored 27 points and had 12 assists to lead No. 25 James Madison to an 86-54 win over Lafayette on Tuesday night in the semifinals of the JMU Invitational.

Tarik Hislop added 15 points for the Dukes (9-1), who outrebounded Lafayette 38-19 and shot 57.6 percent from the floor. Nichelle Glover had 11 points and seven rebounds

The Leopards (2-10) led 17-15 with 9:40 left in the first period, but James Madison went on an 8-2 run to take the lead for good.

Lauren Jackson led Lafayette with 17 points. LaKeisha Wright added 11 and Melissa Downey had 10.
